# Generation Instructions for guides/visual-design.md

## Context

You are generating the visual design guide - a high-level checklist of design principles, system foundations, and quality standards.

This file serves as:
- **Design philosophy** documentation
- **Quality checklist** for UI/UX
- **Design system principles** (not specific values)
- **Accessibility standards** (WCAG compliance)

**Audience**: Frontend developers, designers
**Tone**: Principle-focused, quality-oriented, accessible
**Length**: 200-300 lines (focused checklist)

**IMPORTANT**: This file should ONLY be generated if `has_frontend == true`.

## Input Data

```json
{
  "project_name": "string",
  "frontend_framework": "React|Vue|Angular|Svelte|..."
}
```

## Output Requirements

### Structure

Generate visual-design.md with these sections:

#### 1. Header
```markdown
# Visual Design Guide - {Project Name}

This guide defines design principles, quality standards, and the foundation for UI/UX in {Project Name}.

**Philosophy**: User-first, meticulous craft, speed, simplicity, accessibility.
```

#### 2. Core Design Philosophy & Strategy

**Checklist format** (use checkboxes):
- [ ] **Users First**: Prioritize user needs, workflows, and ease of use in every design decision
- [ ] **Meticulous Craft**: Aim for precision, polish, and high quality in every UI element
- [ ] **Speed & Performance**: Design for fast load times and snappy, responsive interactions
- [ ] **Simplicity & Clarity**: Strive for clean, uncluttered interface with unambiguous labels
- [ ] **Focus & Efficiency**: Help users achieve goals quickly with minimal friction
- [ ] **Consistency**: Maintain uniform design language (colors, typography, components) across application
- [ ] **Accessibility (WCAG AA+)**: Design for inclusivity with sufficient contrast, keyboard nav, screen reader support
- [ ] **Thoughtful Defaults**: Establish clear, efficient default workflows, reducing decision fatigue

#### 3. Design System Foundation (Tokens & Components)

**Define a Color Palette** (checklist):
- [ ] **Primary Brand Color**: User-specified, used strategically
- [ ] **Neutrals**: A scale of grays (5-7 steps) for text, backgrounds, borders
- [ ] **Semantic Colors**: Define Success (green), Error/Destructive (red), Warning (yellow/amber), Informational (blue)
- [ ] **Dark Mode Palette**: Create corresponding accessible dark mode palette
- [ ] **Accessibility Check**: Ensure all color combinations meet WCAG AA contrast ratios (4.5:1 for text, 3:1 for UI components)

#### 4. Typography System

**Typography Checklist:**
- [ ] **Font Families**: Define sans-serif system (readable, modern) and monospace (code)
- [ ] **Type Scale**: Establish harmonious size progression (8-10 sizes minimum)
- [ ] **Font Weights**: Use 3-4 weights (normal, medium, semibold, bold)
- [ ] **Line Heights**: Define tight (headings), normal (body), relaxed (long-form)
- [ ] **Hierarchy**: Clear visual distinction between heading levels
- [ ] **Readability**: Minimum 16px base size, adequate line spacing
- [ ] **Consistency**: Use type scale consistently across all components

#### 5. Spacing System

**Spacing Checklist:**
- [ ] **Base Unit**: Establish consistent base (4px or 8px recommended)
- [ ] **Scale**: Create 10-12 spacing values following consistent progression
- [ ] **Component Spacing**: Define standards for internal component padding
- [ ] **Layout Spacing**: Define standards for margins between sections
- [ ] **Consistency**: Use spacing scale exclusively (no arbitrary values)
- [ ] **Responsive**: Adjust spacing appropriately for mobile vs desktop

#### 6. Layout & Grid

**Layout Checklist:**
- [ ] **Container Widths**: Define max-widths for different viewport sizes (sm, md, lg, xl)
- [ ] **Grid System**: Establish flexible grid (12-column recommended)
- [ ] **Breakpoints**: Define mobile, tablet, desktop breakpoints
- [ ] **Mobile First**: Design for mobile, progressively enhance
- [ ] **Responsive Behavior**: Content adapts gracefully to all screen sizes
- [ ] **Touch Targets**: Minimum 44x44px tap targets on mobile

#### 7. Component Library Principles

**Core Components Checklist:**

**Buttons:**
- [ ] Define 3-5 variants (primary, secondary, outline, ghost, danger)
- [ ] Support 3 sizes (small, medium, large)
- [ ] Include all states (default, hover, active, disabled, loading)
- [ ] Ensure adequate padding and touch targets
- [ ] Consistent styling across all variants

**Inputs & Forms:**
- [ ] Cover all input types (text, email, password, number, textarea, select)
- [ ] Define states (default, focus, error, disabled, read-only)
- [ ] Always pair with labels (accessibility requirement)
- [ ] Show clear error messages below inputs
- [ ] Support keyboard navigation
- [ ] Use aria attributes appropriately

**Cards:**
- [ ] Define anatomy (header, body, footer)
- [ ] Create variants (default, interactive, outlined, elevated)
- [ ] Consistent padding and spacing
- [ ] Responsive behavior

**Modals/Dialogs:**
- [ ] Trap focus inside modal
- [ ] Close on ESC key
- [ ] Prevent body scroll when open
- [ ] Use proper ARIA roles (role="dialog", aria-modal="true")
- [ ] Clear visual hierarchy (header, body, footer)

**Alerts/Notifications:**
- [ ] Define semantic types (success, warning, error, info)
- [ ] Consistent color coding
- [ ] Icons for quick recognition
- [ ] Dismissible option
- [ ] Appropriate positioning

**Tables:**
- [ ] Use semantic HTML elements
- [ ] Sortable columns
- [ ] Responsive strategy (scroll or stack)
- [ ] Accessible headers (scope attribute)
- [ ] Pagination for large datasets

**Component Documentation:**
- [ ] Every component has clear API/props
- [ ] Usage examples provided
- [ ] Accessibility notes included
- [ ] All variants documented

#### 8. Icons & Imagery

**Icons Checklist:**
- [ ] **Consistent Library**: Choose one icon set (Heroicons, Lucide, Material, etc.)
- [ ] **Size Scale**: Define 4-5 icon sizes (16px to 48px)
- [ ] **Visual Weight**: Icons match typography weight
- [ ] **Accessibility**: Provide alt text for meaningful icons
- [ ] **Decorative Icons**: Use aria-hidden="true" for decorative icons
- [ ] **Color**: Icons use semantic colors or inherit from parent

**Imagery:**
- [ ] **Quality Standards**: High-resolution images, optimized for web
- [ ] **Aspect Ratios**: Define standard ratios (16:9, 4:3, 1:1)
- [ ] **Alt Text**: All images have descriptive alt attributes
- [ ] **Loading Strategy**: Lazy load below fold, eager load above

#### 9. Shadows & Elevation

**Shadows Checklist:**
- [ ] **Elevation Scale**: Define 4-6 shadow levels (subtle to prominent)
- [ ] **Purposeful Use**: Shadows indicate elevation and interactivity
- [ ] **Consistency**: Apply shadows consistently to similar components
- [ ] **Dark Mode**: Adjust shadows for dark backgrounds
- [ ] **Performance**: Use box-shadow sparingly for performance

#### 10. Borders & Radius

**Borders Checklist:**
- [ ] **Border Widths**: Define 2-3 widths (1px, 2px, 4px)
- [ ] **Border Colors**: Use from color palette (neutral grays, semantic colors)
- [ ] **Consistent Application**: Borders indicate boundaries and focus states
- [ ] **Border Radius**: Define 5-6 radius values (sm to full circle)
- [ ] **Visual Cohesion**: Use consistent radius across similar components

#### 11. Animation & Motion

**Motion Checklist:**
- [ ] **Purposeful Motion**: Animations provide feedback or guide attention
- [ ] **Timing**: Define 3 duration speeds (fast ~150ms, normal ~300ms, slow ~500ms)
- [ ] **Easing**: Use appropriate easing (ease-in, ease-out, ease-in-out)
- [ ] **Subtlety**: Keep animations subtle, not distracting
- [ ] **Performance**: Use transform and opacity for 60fps animations
- [ ] **Accessibility**: Respect prefers-reduced-motion media query
- [ ] **Consistency**: Similar interactions use consistent timing/easing

#### 12. Accessibility Standards (WCAG 2.1 AA)

**Accessibility Checklist:**
- [ ] **Color Contrast**: Text 4.5:1, large text 3:1, UI components 3:1 minimum
- [ ] **Keyboard Navigation**: All interactive elements keyboard accessible
- [ ] **Focus Indicators**: Visible focus states on all focusable elements
- [ ] **Tab Order**: Logical, intuitive tab sequence
- [ ] **Semantic HTML**: Use proper HTML elements (button, nav, main, etc.)
- [ ] **ARIA Labels**: Add when semantic HTML insufficient
- [ ] **Alt Text**: Descriptive alternative text for all meaningful images
- [ ] **Screen Reader Testing**: Test with VoiceOver/NVDA/JAWS
- [ ] **Focus Management**: Trap focus in modals, return on close
- [ ] **Skip Links**: Provide skip navigation for keyboard users
- [ ] **Live Regions**: Announce dynamic content changes
- [ ] **Form Labels**: Every input has associated label

#### 13. Dark Mode (Optional)

**Dark Mode Checklist:**
- [ ] **Color Palette**: Create dark mode variants for all colors
- [ ] **Contrast**: Maintain WCAG AA contrast in dark mode
- [ ] **System Preference**: Detect and respect prefers-color-scheme
- [ ] **User Override**: Allow manual theme toggle
- [ ] **Persistence**: Remember user's theme choice
- [ ] **Smooth Transition**: Animate theme changes subtly
- [ ] **Testing**: Test all components in dark mode

#### 14. Responsive Design Principles

**Responsive Checklist:**
- [ ] **Mobile First**: Design for mobile, enhance for larger screens
- [ ] **Breakpoints**: Define clear breakpoints (mobile, tablet, desktop)
- [ ] **Fluid Layouts**: Use percentage/viewport units, not fixed pixels
- [ ] **Touch Targets**: Minimum 44x44px (iOS) or 48x48px (Android)
- [ ] **Target Spacing**: Adequate space between touch targets
- [ ] **Content Priority**: Most important content visible on small screens
- [ ] **Images**: Responsive images with appropriate sizes
- [ ] **Testing**: Test on real devices, not just browser resize

#### 15. Design Tokens & Documentation

**Design Tokens Checklist:**
- [ ] **Centralized Tokens**: Export design system as tokens (JSON/CSS variables)
- [ ] **Token Categories**: Colors, spacing, typography, shadows, radii
- [ ] **Naming Convention**: Semantic names (primary, error) over literal (blue, red)
- [ ] **Version Control**: Track design token changes
- [ ] **Documentation**: Document token usage and purpose

**Component Documentation:**
- [ ] **API Documentation**: Every component has props/API documented
- [ ] **Usage Examples**: Show common use cases
- [ ] **Variants Catalog**: All variants visible in documentation
- [ ] **Accessibility Notes**: Document keyboard shortcuts, ARIA usage
- [ ] **Do's and Don'ts**: Visual examples of correct and incorrect usage

